Report from the headquarters of the Alliance of Three Races.   An assault group of 11 agents entered the bunker with the goal of pursuing and destroying the scientist.  Additional task: scout and report to headquarters about the production of skibidi toilets.  The assault group began an operation codenamed "Circles of Hell".  Group commander: Cameraman grenade launcher.  After completing an additional task, the group commander died a heroic death.  Plunger took command.  The group went down to the lower floors where experiments were being carried out on the toilets.  During the assault, the scientist releases his experimental subjects to destroy the agents.  In the unequal battle, only 5 agents from the assault group survived.  The survivors used the elevator to get to the scientist, but were blocked by the suicide bomber's toilet.  Another agent dies heroically, dragging the suicide bomber downstairs.  When a group of four agents reached the desired floor, they came across an enemy patrol.  After chasing the enemy, the assault group found a warehouse of trophies.  In it, agents found drawings of TVmen technology.  The last words of the red cameraman:  â€œAre they on the same page? Or... Really... he gave it to them...â€  After these words, he dies at the hands of the collectorâ€™s saboteur.  During the skirmish, two agents and a saboteur are killed.  He used television for hypnosis.  To create such technology, he could take knowledge from these drawings.  How they got into the hands of the toilets is unknown.  Plunger man and Speaker man.  The last survivors of the assault group discovered the scientist and entered into battle.  The main Alliance forces joined in the battle and destroyed the main nerve center of the toilet army.  Scientist.  The losses of the Alliance, despite the improved equipment of the agents, are colossal.  During the operation, in some places of the underground base of toilets, the recording of one Vantuz man disappeared.  There are doubts that this is not a jammer.  Someone must have hacked his account.  It is unknown what Vantuz saw, but it remains a mystery.  Expertise is already working on this topic.  Operation "Circles of Hell" was completed with the victory of the Alliance, but at the cost of an assault group of all 11 agents.   Prepared the report: Agent Max92101.

pls new man
The Eurovision Song Contest (French: Concours Eurovision de la chanson), often known simply as Eurovision or by its initialism ESC, is an international song competition organised annually by the European Broadcasting Union. Each participating country submits an original song to be performed live and transmitted to national broadcasters via the Eurovision and Euroradio networks, with competing countries then casting votes for the other countries' songs to determine a winner.  The contest was inspired by and based on Italy's national Sanremo Music Festival, held in the Italian Riviera since 1951. Eurovision has been held annually since 1956 (apart from 2020), making it the longest-running international music competition on TV and one of the world's longest-running television programmes. Active members of the EBU and invited associate members are eligible to compete; as of 2023, 52 countries have participated at least once. Each participating broadcaster sends one original song of three minutes duration or less to be performed live by a singer or group of up to six people aged 16 or older. Each country awards 1â€“8, 10 and 12 points to their ten favourite songs, based on the views of an assembled group of music professionals and the country's viewing public, with the song receiving the most points declared the winner. Other performances feature alongside the competition, including a specially-commissioned opening and interval act and guest performances by musicians and other personalities, with past acts including Cirque du Soleil, Madonna, Justin Timberlake, Mika, Rita Ora and the first performance of Riverdance. Originally consisting of a single evening event, the contest has expanded as new countries joined (including countries outside of Europe, such as Israel and Australia), leading to the introduction of relegation procedures in the 1990s, before the creation of semi-finals in the 2000s. As of 2023, Germany has competed more times than any other country, having participated in all but one edition, while Ireland and Sweden both hold the record for the most victories, with seven wins each in total.  Traditionally held in the country which won the preceding year's event, the contest provides an opportunity to promote the host country and city as a tourist destination. Thousands of spectators attend each year, along with journalists who cover all aspects of the contest, including rehearsals in venue, press conferences with the competing acts, in addition to other related events and performances in the host city. Alongside the generic Eurovision logo, a unique theme is typically developed for each event. The contest has aired in countries across all continents; it has been available online via the official Eurovision website since 2001. Eurovision ranks among the world's most watched non-sporting events every year, with hundreds of millions of viewers globally. Performing at the contest has often provided artists with a local career boost and in some cases long-lasting international success. Several of the best-selling music artists in the world have competed in past editions, including ABBA, Celine Dion, Julio Iglesias, Cliff Richard and Olivia Newton-John; some of the world's best-selling singles have received their first international performance on the Eurovision stage.  While having gained popularity with the viewing public in both participating and non-participating countries, the contest has also been the subject of criticism for its artistic quality as well as a perceived political aspect to the event. Concerns have been raised regarding political friendships and rivalries between countries potentially having an impact on the results. Controversial moments have included participating countries withdrawing at a late stage, censorship of broadcast segments by broadcasters, as well as political events impacting participation. Likewise, the contest has also been criticised for an over-abundance of elaborate stage shows at the cost of artistic merit. Eurovision has, however, gained popularity for its kitsch appeal, its musical span of ethnic and international styles, as well as emergence as part of LGBT culture, resulting in a large, active fanbase and an influence on popular culture. The popularity of the contest has led to the creation of several similar events, either organised by the EBU or created by external organisations; several special events have been organised by the EBU to celebrate select anniversaries or as a replacement due to cancellation.

Hello dafu
Good
I cannot believe how far we have gotten from a meme to a full animation that should be on Netflix. So for the anniversary of skibidi toilet, i think that i should make a summary.  Legend speaks of an ancient civilization that possessed great knowledge and power over plumbing and waste management. These skilled engineers and scientists, known as the Sanitarians, developed advanced technologies to ensure clean and efficient sanitation systems throughout their empire.    Unbeknownst to them, their pursuit of perfection inadvertently unleashed a terrible curse upon their civilization. In their quest to create the ultimate toilet, they delved into forbidden realms of magic and dark alchemy. They sought to infuse their creations with supernatural properties, believing it would enhance their functionality and hygiene. In their arrogance, the Sanitarians performed a ritual that opened a gateway to a realm beyond comprehension-the Wasteland of Chaos.    From this twisted dimension, a malevolent entity known as the Fifth Lord emerged, corrupting their creations and bestowing them with a cursed sentence. The first Skibidi Toilet, the result of this fusion, possessed an insatiable hunger for human waste. As unsuspecting individuals used these newly crafted toilets, they unknowingly became hosts to the Skibidi toilet plague. The curse swiftly spread, transforming the infected into grotesque beings with toilet-like features. With each infected person, the curse grew stronger, and the Skibidi toilets multiplied exponentially. They absorbed the essence of their hosts, melding them with their structure and gaining their abilities. The infected became part of the Skibidi toilet hive mind, forever lost to their human selves. The Sanitarians decided to become the army called Cameramen to stop this war. The toilets were spreading from toilets to urinals. Our army had no idea of how to stop this madness. The toilets were starting to grow larger and larger by the week. A few days later, we found out their weakness by flushing their toilets, but then we were caught by their boss known as the G-Man Toilet. We gained a larger cameraman that was more powerful but while we thought we were winning, G-Man Toilet gained laser eyes and would destroy things in his path. We gained a giant turret to stop the flying giant toilets. Me and my fellow cameraman went to G-Mans boss meeting but then we were exposed and they didn't make it out alive sadly. Some toilets started to have multiple heads and I almost died to one, but a new army called the Speakermen saved me and we were winning. A Speakman led all of the toilets in that following area into a trap with a Giant Speaker Spider. Right when we almost died, We were saved by the new Titan Cameraman. Titan Cameraman almost defeated G-Man but he was injured badly and had to be repaired. The next day, we were flushing so many toilets when I almost died to a Giant toilet, but then a Large Speakerman saved me luckily, suddenly a giant robber toilet came out of nowhere and we all thought that we would die. But luckily, we were saved by the Titan Speakerman. G-Man Toilet hired a scientist toilet to test their abilities with their parasitic toilets and infected the Cameramen and the Speakermen. Suddenly, our Titan Speakerman got infected and was a part of the toilets army for a long time. We developed a cure gun for the infected, but then G-Man Toilet found out and we were struck. 3 days later, I almost died but then I was saved by a TV Man. The next day, we were introduced to a Large TV Man who could kill almost everything in sight as long as we were wearing a lens cap. Some toilets came the next day to invade but then suddenly, a new titan came and he was called Titan TV Man.    Titan TV Man could defeat every single thing in the path with the powers of his giant monitor. Titan TV Man then defeated some more toilets but then he saw the infected Titan Speakerman and we knew that our Titan TV Man would easily uninfect the Titan Speakerman and we would all be good. We faced G-Man Toilet and we almost flushed G-Man Toilet with the power of Titan TV Man's monitor, but suddenly, Infected Titan Speakerman came and stabbed Titan TV Man's Monitor and the Toilets demolished Titan TV Man luckily he fled so he wouldn't get infected. We saw that we were struck and the toilets kept invading. Some toilets even have lasers, guns, jetpacks, claws, nunchucks, and even buzzsaws that would demolish our team. Suddenly, were introduced to TV Woman and she got rid of the buzzsaws by blowing it up. We saw that more powerful toilets were coming so TV Woman teleported me to the camera base. Suddenly, the base was invaded by Fire artillery toilets, we had plunger man to stop the madness, and then, The brand newly brand new Upgraded Titan Cameraman defeated all of the buzzsaw and artillery toilets. Plungerman was defeating the army of toilets and we met Camerawoman who had a gun inside of the powerful camera head. A few days later, we saw the Upgraded infected Titan Speakerman invading our army. My friend experienced this and he was killed by Titan Speakerman's very powerful speakers. We sent out a tank that could kill the toilets, but then the tank was destroyed by a giant mutant skull toilet that had radioactive breath that could kill most. Luckily, Titan Cameraman saved us by defeating the toilet into the ground. We knew we would be out of time. The days passed until the day when we would finally cure Titan Speakerman. The secret agent (Dafuq?! Boom!), put us on a mission. Eventually, we found Titan Speakerman and we cured him by taking out the parasite toilet. We cured him but suddenly, G-Man Toilet came and tried to destroy us until he found out that Titan Speakerman was cured, so he fled. The next day, Titan Speakerman felt bad about all the trouble he had caused, so he decided to get revenge on all of the toilets. Titan Cameraman suddenly came but all of the toilets in the area were cleared out by Titan Speakerman, so Titan Cameraman had to catch up. This madness will finally end soon. At the start of Day 59, our army was flushing toilets and saving the Cameramen, but suddenly a Giant Bomber Rocket Toilet came and started invading the city. We knew that we could not defeat him, but then Titan Cameraman and Titan Speakerman came to destroy The Giant Toilet while Titan Cameraman came to defeat all of the surrounding Flying Tri-Artillarist Astro Toilets. And guess what, we finally took back the city. All of the toilets we scared and fled to warn the boss. G-Man  Toilet 3.0 found out and wasn't very happy about this, but he was planning an ambush for the Titans. While The Titans were defeating the toilets, a Large TV Man suddenly showed up and showed all of us footage that some cameramen found, so we saw what happened and it was not looking good. The Titans saw what had happened  and they went to go attack the toilets.     When it was the night or 26' September 23, I was looking  around and I was disabling some chainsaw bizarre toilets. Suddenly, I saw the Penguin-Zero toilet, it blinded all of the cameramen in sight and decapitated their heads and I was shocked. But next was shocking when the Penguin-Zero toilet almost killed me, next, Speakerwoman suddenly came and defeated the toilet with some kn#ves. Later, we were ambushed by some mutant toilets and the main powerful toilets such as G-Man and Scientist toilets. Day 63 of this log, this has been a rough journey of pain in our place. The group and I found and area to camp in, suddenly i turned around and notices that a toilet with massive powerful sharp claws had stabbed insidevof a cameramans back which killed him unfortanuntly, I was worried and decided to run. The toilet saw me and was heading straight for me, I fell down as he came closer, luckily a Dark Speakerman stabbed the toilet in the eye and I was saved. I asked him to help me up off the ground, but he refused so instead I just got up myself. The next few camera turrets were moving foward but then the mutant toilet demolished the tank and those passangers died. We thought we were dead until Plungerman came with new upgrades and started ganging up of the mutant toilet until he fell to the floor in so much pain. He landed from his upgraded machine and came out. He saw that Lucky Cameraman was laughing and plungerman threw a plunger at his face and did the middle finger to him. As i watched i gave him a thumbs up and he gave me a thumbs up as well. The mutant suddenly got back up to get revenge and behind him was a large speakerman that lost his left arm. The large speakerman stabbed the mutant toilet in the eye and he died and was flushed. And we were saved.
